reviews.review: So many things get explained.. great story.

Was expecting the worst, based on all the poor media reviews, but was pleasantly surprised. Had a relatively neat story arc that wrapped up all the loose ends and salvaged the storyline after Ryan Johnson's demolition derby of all things Star Wars. Actually cared a bit for the characters for the first time in the new trilogy and the final scenes were actually pretty awesome. Overall well worth watching.

10/10! The best of the new trilogy and up there for the series as a whole honestly. Packed full of action, classic awe inspiring "star wars" moments and laughs. Forget the critics squabbling over wether or not this movie is "a disservice" to the previous film (The Last Jedi) and *please* stop trying to interject social commentary into these movies. It's Star Wars! It's not right that we live in a world where people are afraid to criticize a movie because they'll get labeled "anti-progressive" by the social media group-think mobs. Why does everything need to be so political these days lol. Narratively speaking, the previous film had objectively poor storytelling and did little to advance the plot of the trilogy overall. It also did little to advance the development of these great new characters we were given in The Force Awakens. The Rise of Skywalker not only course corrects all of this, but adds to the overall narrative in new and intriguing ways!!

A good conclusion to the series, and way better than the prequels.  I was impressed how well they fit scenes involving Leah into the flow.  Hard to tell how much was spare footage from earlier out-takes and how much was CGA.
Loved it! Lots of action and fantastic story line. Dud not dissapoint. I probably enjoyed this one the most if all of them. Was easier to follow.
An honest embarrassment to the Star Wars franchise. Completely disregards Lucas' work of the other six films, and degrades the Prequel/Original trilogy to no end.
Classic Star Wars story line and fight/battle scenes. I enjoyed the throw-back cameo appearances, since I've been watching Star Wars movies for more than 40 years!

I was disappointed. I've seen all eight episodes, also Rogue One and I also went to see the reissues of episodes 4, 5 and 6 and I felt that episode 9 didn't live up to the hype or the anticipation. The only reason that I might recommend it is if someone has already seen the first eight episodes, then go and see it, that way you'll at least have seen the entire Star Wars saga. If you haven't kept up with the previous episodes, then don't waste your money. I'm sure that I'll get lots of loyal Star Wars fans that will disagree with me but that's my opinion.
Very enjoyable forget what some of the nerds and critics say
